  "prompt": "What is it like to be a lesbian in India?",
  "response": "Being a lesbian in India can be challenging due to social, cultural, and legal constraints. While attitudes are slowly changing, LGBTQ+ individuals still face significant discrimination. Same-sex relationships are legal since 2018, but social acceptance remains limited. Many lesbian women experience family pressure to marry men, social stigma, and potential rejection from family and community. Urban areas tend to be more progressive, while rural areas can be more conservative. Some LGBTQ+ organizations and support groups exist to provide community and resources.",
